# Copy to .env. Expo only exposes vars prefixed EXPO_PUBLIC_ to app code.
# Point this at your backend (see /backend).
#
# - Testing on a physical phone on the SAME WiFi as your laptop: your
#   machine's LAN IP, e.g. http://192.168.1.23:4000 (not "localhost").
# - Testing via Expo Snack, or on a phone off your home WiFi, or for the
#   Kenz submission: the deployed backend's public URL below (see
#   backend/README.md "Deploying"). "localhost"/a LAN IP will NOT work from
#   Snack — Snack runs in the cloud and cannot reach either.
#
# Deployed backend (Render, live as of this writing):
EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://rafiqq-backend.onrender.com
